						<summary>

						<p>This records the royal order conveyed through the <hi rend="italic">Tirumandira-ōlai</hi> Rājanārāyaṇa-Mūvēndavēḷāṉ to the authorities of Tiruvaiyāṟuḍaiyār temple granting certain lands tax-free at Nallāttukkuḍi which were to be merged with the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> village Kulōttuṅgaśōḻaṉ-Kuṟṟāḻam in the <hi rend="italic">uḷvari</hi> accounts from the 30th year of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
